parameters.name: options
parameters.description:
An object that has the following properties:

cause Optional


          A property indicating the specific cause of the error.
          When catching and re-throwing an error with a more-specific or useful error message, this property can be used to pass the original error.

parameters.name: cause
parameters.description:
A property indicating the specific cause of the error.
          When catching and re-throwing an error with a more-specific or useful error message, this property can be used to pass the original error.

parameters.name: fileName
parameters.description: The name of the file containing the code that caused the exception

parameters.name: lineNumber
parameters.description: The line number of the code that caused the exception

name: TypeError.prototype.constructor
description: The constructor function that created the instance object. For TypeError instances, the initial value is the TypeError constructor.

name: TypeError.prototype.name
description: Represents the name for the type of error. For TypeError.prototype.name, the initial value is "TypeError".
